This article is a transcript of a press gaggle by Deputy Press Secretary Bill Burton on Air Force One. In the gaggle, Burton discusses an upcoming town meeting, where the President will talk about the economy and healthcare reform. He also addresses the disruptions and protests that have been happening at previous town halls, stating that while the President encourages spirited debate, disruptive behavior is not productive. Burton also briefly discusses General McChrystal's comments about the situation in Afghanistan and the President's strategy in the region. The article concludes with information about the President's upcoming schedule, including more town halls on healthcare reform.